How We Use Your Data
Our Services may contain links to third-party websites or social media platforms where you can share information. Using these platforms may result in the collection of your data by those third parties. We encourage you to review their privacy policies and settings to understand how your data is handled. Below are the key ways we use your information:
To Provide Services
: We need certain information to fulfill the services you request. This includes your device information and contact details, which may be shared with our service providers as necessary to deliver the services.
To Provide Customer Support
: We process your information to respond to your questions, concerns, disputes, or feedback. Without this information, we wouldn’t be able to assist you effectively.
To Enforce Terms and Policies
: We use your data to monitor, investigate, and prevent unauthorized or illegal activities, violations of our policies, and to enforce our agreements with partners.
For Security Purposes
: Your information helps us improve security measures, combat spam, malware, and unauthorized access to your account. Without this information, we cannot ensure the safety of our services.
Data Protection
We are committed to protecting your personal information through physical, technical, and administrative safeguards. Our service providers also adhere to these same protective measures. However, we cannot guarantee that unauthorized access, loss, misuse, or alteration of your data won’t happen.
It’s also important that you take responsibility for securing your information. When you create an account, choose a secure password and keep it confidential. Avoid leaving your device unlocked, and make sure you trust the wireless connections you use to access our services.
Third-Party Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or transfer your Personally Identifiable Information to outside parties. However, we may share your data with partners and service providers who assist in operating our app or serving you, as long as these parties agree to keep your information confidential. We may also release information when necessary to comply with legal obligations, enforce our policies, or protect our rights and safety.
Non-personally identifiable visitor information may, however, be shared with third parties for marketing, advertising, or other uses.
Third-Party Links
Our website does not contain or offer third-party products or services.
