End of Trial and Subscription Renewal
:
Pricing is set for customers in the United States. Prices may vary in other countries, and charges will be converted to your local currency. Payment is charged to your Google Account at the time of purchase.
Subscriptions renew automatically unless auto-renew is turned off at least 24 hours before the end of the current period.
Managing Subscriptions
:
Users can manage their subscriptions in the account settings, where auto-renewal can be turned off. Any unused portion of a free trial period will be forfeited when you purchase a subscription.
Cancellation of Trial or Subscription
You can cancel auto-renewal for your subscription anytime through the Google Play Store. After your current trial or subscription period ends, you will be unsubscribed. You cannot cancel an active subscription. When your subscription expires, you will no longer have access to the included features.
